      How to connect to APP

      1. Download the APP by scanning QR or searching. （Android5.0 or iOS 13.0 or above）
      2. Turn on the plug and put it close to the router when start pairing with APP.（Set your WiFi as 2.4G Wi-Fi for successful pairing）
      3. Press and hold the power button for 5-10 seconds until the indicator light will rapidly blink fast, EZ mode is available and wait for connected.

      Or try the second way, re-press and hold the on/off button for 5 seconds when the indicator blinking fast, then indicator light become blinking slow, AP mode is available and wait for connected.

      • Note: When the smart plug changed network environment, you need to restore the factory settings (Remove the socket from outlet and plug in again, press and hold on to the power button for about 5-10 seconds), and then reconnect to the network.
      • Opening Bluetooth on your phone makes it easier to connect your device to the app, It's not necessary.
      • Only support 2.4Ghz WiFi while connecting with APP. Apply to home appliances which Max load power1800W,15A, please check the load of your appliance before plugging in.
      • Once connected, you can use your phone via 4G or 5G Wi-Fi to turn on/off the smart life outlet anywhere, Please keep the smart extension stay on 2.4G Wi-Fi range always.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      • Nash D.
        1.0 out of 5 stars Overheating Issue with USB Ports - Not Suitable for Multiple High-Draw Devices
        Reviewed in the United States on August 15, 2024
        Style: White-AVerified Purchase
        I purchased the GHome Smart Plug Outlet Extender with high hopes for its versatility and smart features. The ability to control individual outlets and USB ports through Alexa and Google Home was appealing, as was the promise of handling up to 1800W with a 15A rating. However, my experience with this product has been concerning.

        I used the three USB ports to power three neon signs, which should have been a simple task for a product claiming to support 5V/3A across the USB ports. After about an hour of use, the outlet started making a "Sssss" sound, and the area around the USB ports became very hot to the touch. This noise and heat buildup made me fear that it could spark a fire or blow a fuse, so I immediately unplugged everything for safety.

        It's clear that this product struggles to handle multiple devices drawing power from the USB ports simultaneously. If you're planning to use this for anything more than low-power devices, I would be cautious. The overheating issue is not something to take lightly, especially when it comes to home safety.

        While the smart features are nice, they aren't worth the risk of potential electrical hazards. I'll be looking for a more robust solution and would recommend others do the same if they plan to use all the ports at once.

        This product seems to be in high demand—it’s often out of stock or priced way above the 50 CAD mark, compared to the 37 CAD I paid.
